Italy’s UniCredit Seeks Stake in Hrvatski Telekom, Poslovni Says

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-03-31T07:10:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/italy-s-unicredit-seeks-stake-in-hrvatski-telekom-poslovni-says.html
Italy’s  UniCredit SpA (UCG)  and its
Croatian unit Zagrebacka Banka d.d. are interested in obtaining
a stake in Hrvatski Telekom d.d.,  Poslovni Dnevnik  reported,
citing people it didn’t identify.  The bank is negotiating for the 10.5 percent stake of
 Croatia ’s leading telecommunications provider held by Croatia’s
 veterans  and  pension  funds and estimated at 2.5 billion kuna
($480 million), Poslovni said today.  Along with UniCredit, international investments banks  J.P.
Morgan  and Nomura are also interested in obtaining in the
Hrvatski Telekom stake, the Zagreb-based newspaper said,
reiterating its report from Feb. 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  